    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>breaded</strong> <strong>halloumi slices</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until golden and crispy</p><p>Transfer onto kitchen paper to soak up any excess oil – this is your<strong> Southern fried halloumi</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Ordered extra halloumi? Slice and cook in a pan with a little oil for 4-6 min or until golden all over</span></strong></p>",
